  "instructions": [
    "soak corn husks in water for at least 30 minutes.",
    "mix together masa harina and baking soda in a large bowl.",
    "add in corn kernels, onion, garlic, and chili powder; mix until just combined.",
    "in a separate saucepan, melt butter over medium heat; add in tomato and piloncillo; cook until piloncillo dissolves.",
    "add in chicken broth and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.",
    "temper in cocoa powder; stir to combine.",
    "spread a thin layer of masa mixture onto a corn husk; spoon a tablespoon of sauce over the mixture; sprinkle with cotija cheese and cilantro; fold husk over and secure with a strip of corn husk.",
    "steam tamales for 45 minutes; serve in a korean brass bowl."
